&lt;p&gt;A UNIQUE OPPORTUNITY HAS ARISEN FOR A PIONEERING AND FORWARD THINKING HEART FAILURE NURSE&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic nurse who is passionate about providing holistic care and support to patients with both a new and existing diagnosis of Heart failure. The role will involve working across acute in-patient and out-patient settings undertaking patient assessment and implementing management plans. In addition the post holder is expected to participate in the development of education, training and clinical supervision on occasion. If you have an interest in the specialist area of heart failure and can demonstrate sound clinical leadership we would welcome your application. Candidates should have high clinical standards and be committed to quality patient care with previous Heart Failure Service experience. Excellent communication skills are essential for this applicant as they will be a senior member of the heart failure multi-disciplinary team. The applicant will have evidence of teaching patients and staff and personal development which will be evident with the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHY YOU SHOULD WORK FOR US:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great learning and development opportunities to enable all staff to fulfil their potential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary sacrifice schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS agenda for change terms and conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A generous annual leave provision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For any more information please feel free to contact: Louise Green, Cardiology Matron 07976617085&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The informal contact details contained in this advert are for enquiry purposes only. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
